width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thevolcanogod>thevolcanogod</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/7/03 1:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=497.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Message to Those Posting Raid Intents</span><hr size=1> We went to hate the day before The Fellowship had posted an intent to raid – our objective:  to kill Innoruk. He wasn’t up so we left. We left all of the minis up except for Magi P’tassia.<br>
<br>
In regards to reservations – most of you know that I am and have always been a big advocate of the bigger guilds respecting open raids and such. Most of Clan Twisted feels the same way. There was no reason for us to clear Hate – we didn’t need the armor or the experience – we were only there for Inny – so I feel we did the right thing and bugged out when we found he wasn’t up.<br>
<br>
However, due to past problems – most notably a Fear raid which we scheduled and posted here out of respect for everyone else – and were promptly leap-frogged and every mini killed the day before we went up (the guild who did it never came forward to admit it and save us the trouble of breaking in either) – we aren’t posting our raids in advance anymore. We feel bad about this because it will eventually cause problems between us and the open raids and guilds who still post intents. But we feel this is a necessary thing since it was displayed to us that other guilds are using intents as a way to schedule their own raids around planned and posted raids by other guilds in order to ensure that content will be available to them. Please note that we will never follow this practice – we plan things on our own timetables and will not intentionally leap-frog another raid.<br>
<br>
We will always respect FCFS – if your guild is in a plane or assembled and buffing with enough people to enter a plane or kill a creature, we will always stand down and find something else to do. Also, we don’t and have never recognized the legitimacy of intents on single spawns – this includes Trakanon, Gorenaire, Talendor, Phingel, Severilous, Lodizal, Venril Saithir, Va’Dyn, Zelnithak or any other boss-type encounter. We continue to recognize FCFS in regards to these creatures.<br>
<br>
We hope that our policy will have a minimal impact on the community – most of our targets are beyond the capability of open or small-guild raids and we rarely spend time in the old-world planes. However, eventually conflicts will occur and we apologize for any problems that might arise. Open raids are welcome to announce their intentions to raid old-world planes on our message board <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub21.ezboard.com/bclantwisted">pub21.ezboard.com/bclantwisted</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> and if we haven’t scheduled a raid for that location already, we will try to avoid the times you have planned.<br>
 <p>Vulrath Vadrigaar<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=383550">61 Vah Shir Oracle</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
