<br>
Anezkia – that is not the right thing to do and any guild that leapfrogged another like that, I think, would be very much in the wrong. If you are making attempts at something, of course we and I think most other guilds will let you try as many times as you want until you win or give up.<br>
<br>
As for Venril Saithir – to make things short – he is a FCFS creature and nearly everyone recognizes him as such – same with Phinny and Lodizal. You can’t reserve him or “intend to kill him” for a “couple days” – those reservations won’t be accepted. As long as you are there trying to kill him, others will leave you alone – but if you give up for the night, don’t expect everyone to leave him alone for you the next day. That is always how it’s been even on servers with a full-fledged reservation system.<br>
<br>
As Shabba said – one or two people in a zone shouting “X creature is camped – everyone else bugger off” isn’t going to reserve something. There needs to be a decent raid force already there and prepping for the kill. Otherwise you could send out scouts and “reserve” nearly every FCFS target in Kunark, Luclin and Velious permanently with one or two people – no big guilds will recognize this.<br>
<br>
Back on another discussion about reservations, someone put it well – that after a certain level, everything is FCFS and guilds that reach that level have to deal with the jump to FCFS. That’s not saying you don’t have to be disrespectful or play fair, but FCFS is the nature of the game past a certain point (on this server at least). Guilds must adapt to this – not try to bleed the “intent” system over and start trying to reserve stuff that has always been FCFS here. I’m all about respecting “the little guys” but if a guild gains the coordination and knowledge to take down stuff like Va’Dyn, Trakanon, Venril Saithir and Zlandicar, they are no longer “little guys”.<br>
<br>
We don’t want to beat a dead horse with this and we probably won’t bring it up again because it’s always messy to talk about FCFS versus reservations. We just wanted to let people know that most guilds won’t honor “intents” for FCFS creatures. If it’s up, kill it – if you can’t or don’t want to and someone gets there first, congratulate them. <p>Vulrath Vadrigaar<br>
