<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=561580" target="top">www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=561580</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sirdo>Sirdo</A> at: 4/8/03 11:31:34 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=roenelin>Roenelin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/8/03 3:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=497.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Message to Those Posting Raid Intents</span><hr size=1> Greetings, all.<br>
<br>
It's always refreshing to read through a message string full of inteligent and focussed posts, intended not to ridicule but to inform and discuss.<br>
<br>
I have only recently entered into the grand arena of zone raiding in EQ as this is my first time having a character of the season to join in on these raids. As a result, I must rely on the wisdom and knowledge of others around me to guide me along the best path to achieving goals. With this in mind, I look upon these inteligent and pointed posts and I learn how things are and are not done. I am happy to have one or two points to add to this discussion, though I do not expect to change policy.<br>
<br>
In most of the raids I have attended, there is a specific target in mind. In most cases it is an epic quest NPC and is the purpose for the raid taking place. Along the path to this target as well as after the intended target has been defeated, there are often what could be considered Targets of Opportunity, some of which can be avoided (as seen in Vulrath's initial post describing CT's brief trip to Hate) and others that simply cannot (I'm thinking of the Black Reavers in CoM that are in the way of about every other epic NPC in the zone). In the zones where there are optional Targets of Opportunity, it is very easy for an &quot;Intent&quot; driven raid force to convert to a FCFS raid force who should consider the upcoming plans of the next &quot;Intent&quot; raid. Obviously it takes a given amount of time for each epic NPC to respawn and this Intent board should be refered to in such cases to ensure that one guild's week or two of advance notice and preparation are not wasted because theirs was a Target of Opportunity for another group.<br>
<br>
Vulrath, I'm saddened to hear that there are those who would use CT's posts of intention to beat &quot;the big guys&quot; to the prize. Truely there is no honor in that kind of gameplay and it detracts from the enjoyment of those who come to spend a few hours away from RL. Certainly CT has members who also need epic quest pieces and want other high level loot and should be afforded the opportunity to aquire them. Perhaps as a compromise, CT would be willing to post intentions on epic NPCs to keep the rest of us informed, and leave the high-level loot NPCs in the FCFS category. I have yet to read a reply on such a post that is anything but encouraging and informative, and an individual's persuit of their epic weapon seems to hold the interest of the entire community.<br>
<br>
Happily, Firiona Vie is a server with a relatively small population of active characters. I recall reading about the larger servers where a group would have to reserve an NPC (just the one target) a month or more in advance. In such an environment it seems that the FCFS policy would be greatly frowned upon. Here, though, we remain blissfully low in population and the FCFS policy does seem quite reasonable when combined with this Intent board. Certainly &quot;the big guys&quot; should have the option of quickly building a raiding party and hunting down a Target of Opportunity. This is the advantage of being part of such a large group. I would simply request that this message board be watched by such a group and enough time be given for the NPC to respawn for the next group intending to make an attempt. I'll use CoM for another example. If one group decides to head to CoM to take on Lord Ghiosk for a shaman in their group, but reads of the intent of another group to slay Neh'Ashiir, the first group should head in a few hours early, or even wait until a few hours have passed to give the Black Reavers enough time to respawn. Killing Black Reavers is a large part of the fun and excitement in a CoM raid, and the supply and demand for Jade Reavers is well known.<br>
<br>
Well, I've bent everyone's ear, as it were, long enough with this post. Perhaps a compromise might be made and policies changed, perhaps not. What is important is that we're all able to have as much fun as we can in the time we have to play.<br>
<br>
Roenelin Holywolf<br>
Pathfinder of Tunare<br>
Peacekeepers Alliance <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=suometar>Suometar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/9/03 3:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=497.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Message to Those Posting Raid Intents</span><hr size=1> The Fellowship is not a guild. The Fellowship is an alliance of nine guilds, each of them doing their own thing most of the time. The Fellowship doesn't mobilize like a guild, at all. Anything that takes more than two groups or so, will have to be planned in advance. <br>
