<br>
Epics are a status symbol, that I understand.  But if roleplaying was more of a priority to me than raiding I do not think I would even worry about my epic.<br>
<br>
Raiding is really the only reason I play this game, to see more and accomplish greater objectives.  I like the challenge and I like to push myself and my friends to do everything I can.  But even being in a raiding style guild my epic will never come before fun.  I would much rather help push a group of guild mates through trials, or kill a new boss mob that we have never dropped than to try and drag people around the place to get pieces for my epic.  If I collect it along the way, great, if not I won't really have much problem with that either.  There are much better drops in the Elementals than epics anywho.<br>
