<br>
This is another thing that gets me.  I will never see the elemental planes.  So, how am I supposed to get this better equipment?  This little line is so often used to blow off the arguments of the non-raiding people.  &quot;There's better in the planes/ToV/VT/whatever.&quot;  How do I get to these places without joining a raiding guild?  I don't.<br>
<br>
Yes, the epic IS a status symbol, and that is exactly why I want it.  Jaranna's goal is to become the most powerful wizard she can.  She is a follower of Solusek Ro.  The Temple has charged her with gathering four staves that are relics of the faith.  She now has one.  She needs the other three.<br>
<br>
That is my reason for wanting the Staff of the Four.  I don;t think it's wrong or even unrealistic.  Maybe it is on this server.  I don't know. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vicairedelestacia@firionavie>Vicaire Delestacia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/10/03 5:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=497.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Message to Those Posting Raid Intents</span><hr size=1> Just because you choose not to join a raiding guild in no ways means you shouldn't be trying for you epic.  I will even go so far as to say if you choose not to join a guild at all that doesn't mean you shouldn't go for you epic. <br>
<br>
In my humble opinion if you are in a raiding guild, and from what I have seen this is true, you don't even need your epic since you can aquire much better gear much more easily.  This is excepting certain classes such as clerics etc.....  <br>
<br>
For a casual player however an epic is probably the best item you might ever obtain.  Realistically, I don't ever see myself obtaining something better than the SK epic.  Additionally, there is a large amount of pride that comes with achieving your epic.  Not as a status symbol, but as a personal goal and even as a goal among a group of very close friends.  <br>
<br>
Personally I hope to achieve my epic in just such a way rather than have it given to me by a guild with no effort at all. Being in an uber guild just to obtain uber items doesn't appeal to everyone as I will personally attest.  In my humble opinion adventuring and tackling content with a group of friends will always be more satisfying.<br>
<br>
Jaranna,<br>
<br>
